   &UR; HAS BRITISH MUSEUM LOST ITS MARBLES? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The museums of the world are full of other countries' art.
Unfortunately, this happy state of affairs was not always brought
about in the proudest of circumstances. Much museum art was
acquired by dubious means, if not by outright looting. So it is
with the controversial Elgin marble sculptures in the British
Museum. Should they be returned to their original home, Greece? In
such matters, alas, the answer isn't set in stone. &QL;
