   &UR; MOVED AS BC-DEEPSOUTH-BUSHGORE-ECONOMIST-450&AMP;add-NYTSF &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ROUTE 66: PRESERVING AMERICA'S BELOVED `MOTHER ROAD' &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There is no other road in the United States like Route 66, none
as treasured in memory, none as much a part of American culture and
mythology, none as mourned at its death _ or as celebrated at its
resurrection. The recent enactment of a Route 66 preservation bill
is a victory not just for the road itself but for the grass roots
over bureaucracy. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Route-66 States: Ill.,Mo.,Okla.,Texas,N.M.,Ariz.,Calif.) &QL;
</P>
