   &UR; Moved as BC-ROUTE-66-REBIRTH-ECONOMIST-NYTSF &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; RED, WHITE AND GREY: WHAT'S THE FUTURE FOR BOOMERS? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   President Bill Clinton, 53, is staring retirement in the face.
The good news is that he has a pension, good health and excellent
prospects for supplementary income. The bad news is that his wife
may not get the job she is angling for in the autumn, and the
family's retirement nest egg has been squandered on unexpected
legal expenses. Such are the facts the Clinton household might
provide to the Health and Retirement Study (HRS), a huge $100
million study on how Americans grow old. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Michigan _ 6th graf) &QL;
</P>
