for the Ethical Treatment of Animals. (Tom Teepen is national
correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ As with the American economy, the rich of the
Dominican Republic are getting richer and the poor are getting
poorer, even desperate. Santo Domingo is undergoing a building
boom, tourism is at its best ever and the Dominican Republic is
seen as the area's fastest-growing economy. Why, then, are there
boat people? (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist for Cox News
Service.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
