   RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   EVANGELISM _ For evangelical Christians, the directive is
clearly laid forth in the Gospels. It's their job to spread the
word of Jesus Christ to ``unreached peoples,'' even people of other
faiths. The year 2000 has given that evangelization effort new
urgency as Christians celebrate the second millennium of Christ's
birth. In the past 10 years, grass-roots prayer movements have
sprung up, linking individual Christian churches with
``unchurched'' corners of the world. Many of those efforts have
been coordinated through AD2000, a Colorado Springs-based
organization that provides information and resources to
evangelistic efforts around the world. (Jesse, Dayton Daily News).
18. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
