<SLUG> BC-SPCL-TRUCKS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ATTN. EDITORS:  

</HEADLINE>
  
 (l and f coding)  
 For Immediate Release
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Trucks have overwhelmed the automotive imagination in America
and the manufacturers have responded with a cornucopia of
selections. In this special package, Globe automotive writers
discuss the truck field for the potential buyer. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-CROSSOVERS (Undated) _ As the line between car, truck,
SUV and minivan has blurred, the era of crossovers has taken hold.
By Jerry Morris.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-FEATURES (Undated) _ Why should you buy a truck-like
vehicle? Conveniences, flexibility, and safety are three good
reasons. Trucks, according to manufacturers, fall into three
categories: pickups, sport utilities, and minivans. By Jerry
Morris. 1040 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-SUVS (Undated) _ The problem with sport utilities is
deciding what an SUV means to you. By Jerry Morris. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-SAFETY (Undated) _ Safety: You can't ignore it when
thinking about a truck or sport utility vehicle. By Jerry Morris.
730 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-BUY (Undated) _ To buy or to lease: that is the question
consumers must consider before they're ready to acquire a new
vehicle. By Jerry Morris. 570 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-MINIVANS (Undated) _ The new minivans not only are great
people-carriers, but also cargo-movers, too. By Jerry Morris. 480
words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-PICKUPS (Undated) _ Buying a truck or SUV can be a lot
more complicated than walking onto a lot and saying, ``I'll take
that one.'' By Bill Griffith. 960 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-COMBATT (Undated) _ It's obvious that Ford's adaptation
of its F-350 Super Duty Crew Cab pickup will give a whole new
meaning to ``Built Ford Tough.'' By Bill Griffith. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCKS-BRIEFS (Undated) _ If the line between cars, trucks and
SUVs is blurred, here's one that will be unmistakable: the
Harley-Davidson F-150 pickup. By Bill Griffith. 530 words.
</P>
<P>
   For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at
the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  All stories will bear the BOS
designator and move under the  &UR; Lifestyle (l)  &LR; and  &UR; Financial (f) &LR; 
category codes.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
