<HEADER>
A9762 &Cx1f; tab-z
r v BC-SLATE-ADVISORY-NYTSF &LR;      03-17 0530
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SLATE-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; WHAT'S BOTHERING ALL THOSE `OUTRAGED' VOTERS? &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; MCCAIN CONSULTANT GETS `HIS' STORY OUT &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; REPUBLICANS SEIZE THE `GORE GAS TAX' ISSUE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; LOS ANGELES BECOMES A MIDWESTERN COLONY AGAIN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The following ``separate buy'' articles from SLATE, the premier
online magazine of politics and culture, are available from the New
York Times Syndicate. Please contact syndicate sales representative
DEBRA WEYDERT at 732-390-4480)
</P>
<P>
   1. WHAT'S BOTHERING ALL THOSE `OUTRAGED' VOTERS?, by Michael
Kinsley
</P>
<P>
   The Party of Inchoate Outrage (made up mostly of fervent Bradley
and McCain supporters) seems to be a permanent feature of the
political landscape. They are, by and large, not poor or black, not
unemployed or disabled. They are living through the most
spectacular economic boom in history, in a nation almost totally
secure, invulnerable, and at peace with the world. Science is
curing major diseases. Yet another record-mild winter is ending.
And they are furious at the politicians for creating this awful
mess.
</P>
<P>
   950 words: Slugged BC-KINSLEY-ANTI-POLITICS-SLATE
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   2. MCCAIN CONSULTANT GETS `HIS' STORY OUT, By Jacob Weisberg
</P>
<P>
   Political consultants always do the same thing when the campaign
is over. If their horse wins, they take full credit. If they lose,
they blame it on the lousy candidate or on his other, inept
advisers. But even by the normal standards of the
political-consulting profession, which ranks ethically somewhere
between personal-injury law and loan-sharking, Mike Murphy's
behavior is stunning.
</P>
<P>
   1,200 words: Slugged BC-FLAWED-CONSULTANT-SLATE
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   3. REPUBLICANS SEIZE THE `GORE GAS TAX' ISSUE, by William
Saletan
</P>
<P>
   For more than a year, pundits have grossly underestimated Al
Gore's prospects of winning the presidency. No matter what you
think of him or how small a role you think he has played, Gore has
the best material arguments any virtual incumbent could hope for:
eight years of relative peace and unprecedented prosperity, lower
crime rates, and other achievements. Republicans would kill to have
that record. And they have no real hope of beating Gore unless an
issue emerges that threatens the current prosperity and can be
linked to the vice president. Now they may have such an issue:
rising gas prices.
</P>
<P>
   1,100 words: Slugged BC-GASSING-GORE-SLATE
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   4. LOS ANGELES BECOMES A MIDWESTERN COLONY AGAIN, by Timothy
Noah
</P>
<P>
   The acquisition of The Los Angeles Times by the Tribune Co. may
or may not damage the paper's editorial quality. But it's certainly
a historic humiliation for Los Angeles. Los Angeles was the cradle
of a new civilization! The L.A. Times was an important tool in this
manifest destiny. Los Angeles was ready to overtake the East Coast.
Now, though, Los Angeles is being recolonized by the same uncouth
prairie-dwellers who populated it in the early part of the 20th
century. The Rust Belt has purchased Times-Mirror! Even in an age
when newspapers don't have the clout they once did, that stings.
</P>
<P>
   550 words: Slugged BC-LOS-ANGELES-HUMBLED-SLATE
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
