<P>
   POLL-2000 (Washington) _ As the curtain rises on the 2000
general election campaign, voters are in a pessimistic mood over
stock market fluctuations, gas prices and killing of a six-year-old
by a six-year-old in Michigan, a new poll says. The bi-partisan
`Battleground'' poll puts Texas Gov. George W. Bush ahead of Vice
President Al Gore 47 percent to 44 percent. But Gore has improved
his image with voters and leads Bush on issues such as Social
Security, health care and education. By DAN FREEDMAN. (To be filed
in the ``w'' and ``p'' categories.)
