   POLITICS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ISSUE-ADS (Washington) _ If you missed the broadcast advertising
campaigns that George W. Bush and Al Gore waged in early primary
states to help secure their parties' presidential nominations, a
multi-million dollar replay is headed your way. The Republican and
Democratic parties _ and allied organizations theoretically acting
independently of the candidates _ are on the verge of mounting the
most expensive broadcast advertising blitz in U.S. history. By
STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
