<P>
   RAP-BROWN-MAIN _ ATLANTA _ Police today identified former Black
Panther leader H. Rap Brown as the man who shot two deputies in
Atlanta Thursday night. Investigators showed one of the wounded
deputies a photo line-up, which included pictures of Brown, now
know as Jamil Abdullah Al-Amin. Deputy Algernon English identified
Al-Amin as the shooter, Atlanta Police Chief Beverly Harvard said.
Deputy Chief C.B. Jackson said Al-Amin was charged with two counts
of aggravated battery in connection with the shootings. Police are
searching for Al-Amin, but he had not been captured by early
afternoon. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
