<P>
   RAIN-WEEKEND _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Question: What do you call it
after two days of rain in most cities? Answer: Monday. It's no
joke. Researchers at Arizona State University have found something
golfers have always suggested: It rains more on weekends. (Dempsey,
Dayton Daily News). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-POPE _ JERUSALEM _ Advancing Pope John Paul's
long-anticipated visit to the Holy Land the last 10 days of the
month. We take an in-depth look at what may be the last trip for
this pontif _ the most well-traveled pope ever, and the only pope
known to an entire generation. He is in failing health, and one
wonders if this is his mecca. What do Christians here think of his
coming? Are special preparations being made by the Israeli,
Jordanian and Palestinian governments? What places will he visit,
and why? (Kaplow, Cox News Service). 30. WITH GRAPHICS: Itinerary
box attached at end of story.
