   &UR; OTHER CULTURE AND ENTERTAINMENT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MISSING-OSCARS (Hollywood) _ It sounds like the plot of a
Hollywood thriller but it's true: Just nine days before this year's
Academy Awards, Oscar has disappeared, the FBI is hunting for him
and a reward of $50,000 has been offered for his return. Academy of
Motion Picture Arts and Sciences officials confirmed Friday that
this year's crop of 55 Oscar statuettes has been stolen from a
transportation company loading dock in the industrial city of Bell,
just south of Los Angeles. (Summary from wires) By Rick Lyman.
</P>
