<P>
   NY-POLICE-SHOOTING (New York) _ In the wake of the shooting
Thursday of an unarmed off-duty security guard on a Manhattan
street, Mayor Rudolph Giuliani notes that the guard had been
arrested on robbery and weapons possession charges, and gives a
general defense of the Police Department, which he says is battling
an upsurge in homicides. The family of the victim, Patrick
Dorismond, meets with Al Sharpton, who says he is seeking to bypass
local prosecutors in the case to have the federal government take
over prosecution. By Robert D. McFadden.
</P>
