health point man on AIDS. He's also an HIV-infected man facing an
uncertain future. ``I'm scared, yes,'' acknowledged Wood, director
of the HIV/AIDS control program for Public Health-Seattle &AMP; King
County.
</P>
<P>
   By Tom Paulson. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   AIDS-VACCINE (Seattle) _ Scientists finally appear on the verge
of being able to checkmate the AIDS virus with a vaccine, and
Seattle is at the epicenter of the effort.
</P>
<P>
   By Carol Smith. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
