<P>
   BOEING-STRIKE (Seattle) _ Boeing, leaders of striking engineers
reach agreement. Members vote Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Byu Paul Nyhan. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-STRIKE-RESPECT (Seattle) _ The contract seems to address
a key concern that Boeing's engineers and technical workers said
they were striking over: respect.
</P>
<P>
   By Paul Nyhan. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-STRIKE-AHEAD (Seattle) _ A strike that few, certainly few
in management, saw coming is bound to leave some long-term effects
on the company. What happens with the company once workers return
to work. Will the strike and its causes be forgotten quickly or
will the resentments linger, affecting morale? Will Boeing's
management be shaken up?
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   DOLPHINS (Undated) _ Maybe it's the smile. Maybe it's the
playful leaps. Maybe the legends that stretch back to Homer. But
the affinity of humans and dolphins is undeniable, as Tim Cahill
proves in his National Geographic coffee-table book ``Dolphins,''
companion to a new IMAX film.
</P>
<P>
   By M.L. Lyke. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-TITUS (Undated) _ Review of ``Titus,'' new comedy starting
Monday night on Fox.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-BIAS (Undated) _ Discovery Channel begins a ``Hate &AMP;
Violence: No Simple Answers'' initiative Monday with ``How Biased
Are You?'' _ an hourlong documentary examining the subtle everyday
situations in which prejudice and hate manifest themselves.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-VECSEY-COLUMN (Tucson, Ariz.) _ On those lovable Bulldogs of
Gonzaga. Can the magic continue?
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-WEST (Salt Lake City) _ LSU won its first game since
Shaquille O'Neal left the college game in 1990. Since that time,
the Tigers had fallen on hard times: their longtime coach, Dale
Brown, was forced out and the program fell to the bottom of the
SEC. They're back this year as the No. 4 seed in the West.
Saturday, they meet No. 5 seed Texas in Salt Lake City.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Moore. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
