<P>
   WORKING-COLUMN (Houston) _ Clever ideas are sometimes born out
of frustration. Marcus Courtney was a contractor at Microsoft and
got upset two years ago when the software industry successfully
lobbied the Washington state Department of Labor and Industries to
allow high-tech companies to pay straight time instead of
time-and-a-half overtime to workers who earn more than $27.63 per
hour. So Courtney started the Washington Alliance of Technology
Workers (washtech.org) to address the issues of contractors who
work at Microsoft. Last year, the group affiliated with the
Communication Workers of America. By L.M. SIXEL. (Already filed.)
