is passed into law as expected and takes effect in September, gay
couples - like Robert Dostis, left, and Chuck Kletecka of Waterbury
Center - would be granted virtually all the state rights, benefits
and responsibilities that heterosexual spouses have, in areas from
child custody to probate law. (Paul O. Boisvert/The New York Times)
