Bill Joy wrote ``Why the Future Doesn't Need Us,'' an article which
appeared in Wired, a magazine that is more used to celebrating the
brave new wired world. Joy, who is a co-founder and chief scientist
of Sun Microsystems and one of the most respected idea men in the
computer field, argues that risks are not only latent in
technology, but in certain celebrations of technology. The dangers
lie not in our technology but in ourselves. (Thor Swift/The New
York Times)
