Dorm. Reicher was ecstatic when Wesleyan accepted her, and doubly
thrilled when she was assigned to her first choice for a residence
hall, a place called West College. She had been particularly drawn
to West College because it advertised itself as a diverse,
multicultural, politically active dorm. Reicher thought it would be
a welcome change from her hometown. Just how different was clearly
evident within her first 24 hours. (James Estrin/The New York
