   (NYT20) GENEVA -- March 17, 2000 -- BIZ-WORLD-SWISSWATCH-2 --
For all its importance to the country's economy, the $10 billion
Swiss watch industry is going through a profound transformation.
The making of movements - the mechanical working parts - has been
steadily migrating out of the country in search of cheaper labor,
leaving only the most expensive models made entirely in
Switzerland. Employees of Franck Muller Watchland worked on luxury
timepieces. (The New York Times)
