killed Dorismond says the officer's gun fired accidentally during a
struggle. (Courtesy of Sturkey family/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) NEW YORK -- March 17, 2000 -- CENSUS-WORKERS -- Every 10
years, the Census Bureau hires an army of census takers -
enumerators, in bureau parlance. On a recent day in Downtown
Brooklyn, prospective census takers sat for the test required of
applicants across the nation. The Census Bureau wants a pool of 2.4
million qualified people from which to hire. (William C. Lopez/The
New York Times)
</P>
