to further their art. The photograph at left (Dallas Museum of
Art/The New York Times) was in Paul Gauguin's collection and is
believed to have been his model for ``Melanchoilic (Faaturuma)'' of
1891. (Nelson-Atkins Museum of Art/The New York Times)
