BIZ-BMW-MOTORCYCLE -- David Robb, the designer of the sexy $20,000
BMW motorcyle that is the company's best-selling model. Before Robb
came along, BMW motorcycles had a reputation for sturdiness, but
not style. The new luxury touring model, the K 1200 LT, is built
for two riders and offers options like a six-disc CD player, a
dual-control heated seat system, heated hand grips, an on-board
computer and cup holders. (Chester Higgins Jr./The New York Times)
