deputies were seriously wounded while serving a warrant at the home
of Jamil Abdullah Al-Amin, known in the 1960s as H. Rap Brown, a
leader of the Black Panther party now a Muslim cleric. The gunman
escaped after the shooting, and sheriff's officials said they were
looking for Al-Amin. (Sunny Sung/Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
